description:
As an API consumer
  I want to receive a confirmation that the API is alive
  So I can verify that the API is operational

elements.name: API responds successfully to a health check

steps.name: the API is available
a GET request is made to the Alive Endpoint
the API response should return a status code of 200
the Health Check response body should contain "Status" with the value "ALIVE-AND-KICKING"

name: API Health Check Endpoint

description:
As a user 
  I want to parse date tokens and receive the computed dates in the API response.
  So that the correct type of string is returned based on the input token in the API response.

elements.name: Parse a date token

steps.name: a valid or invalid date token "INVALIDTOKEN"
a GET request is made to the DateTokenParser Endpoint
the API response for the DateTokenParser Endpoint should return a status code of 400
the response body should contain "Error" with the value "Invalid string token format"

elements.name: Parse a date token

steps.name: a valid or invalid date token "[TODAY]"
a GET request is made to the DateTokenParser Endpoint
the API response for the DateTokenParser Endpoint should return a status code of 200
the response body should contain "ParsedToken" with the value "today"

elements.name: Parse a date token

steps.name: a valid or invalid date token "[TODAY-1YEAR-1MONTH]"
a GET request is made to the DateTokenParser Endpoint
the API response for the DateTokenParser Endpoint should return a status code of 200
the response body should contain "ParsedToken" with the value "one year and one month ago from today"

elements.name: Parse a date token

steps.name: a valid or invalid date token "[TODAY+1YEAR-2MONTH]"
a GET request is made to the DateTokenParser Endpoint
the API response for the DateTokenParser Endpoint should return a status code of 200
the response body should contain "ParsedToken" with the value "one year ahead and two months ago from today"

name: Parse Date Token Endpoint

description:
As a user
    I want to parse tokens and generate strings based on different token formats
    So that the correct type of string is returned based on the input token in the API response.

elements.name: Parse dynamic string tokens

steps.name: the DynamicStringParser endpoint is running
A request with dynamic string token "INVALIDTOKEN" to the DynamicStringParser endpoint
the API response should return a status code of 400 for the DynamicStringParser endpoint
the response should contain "Error" with the value "Invalid string token format"

elements.name: Parse dynamic string tokens

steps.name: the DynamicStringParser endpoint is running
A request with dynamic string token "[ALPHA-NUMERIC-5]" to the DynamicStringParser endpoint
the API response should return a status code of 200 for the DynamicStringParser endpoint
the response should contain "ParsedToken" with the value "An alpha-numeric string of length 5"

elements.name: Parse dynamic string tokens

steps.name: the DynamicStringParser endpoint is running
A request with dynamic string token "[PUNCTUATION-3]" to the DynamicStringParser endpoint
the API response should return a status code of 200 for the DynamicStringParser endpoint
the response should contain "ParsedToken" with the value "A string of punctuation characters of length 3"

elements.name: Parse dynamic string tokens

steps.name: the DynamicStringParser endpoint is running
A request with dynamic string token "[ALPHA-NUMERIC-PUNCTUATION-10-LINES-2]" to the DynamicStringParser endpoint
the API response should return a status code of 200 for the DynamicStringParser endpoint
the response should contain "ParsedToken" with the value "2 lines of strings with each line containing 10 alpha-numeric-punctuation characters"

name: Dynamic String Parser Endpoint

description:
In order to accurately compute dates from token format strings
    As a user of the TokenDateParser class
    I want to be able to input a variety of token strings and get the correct date output

elements.name: Parsing today - [STARTDATE][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART]

steps.name: A date token "[TODAY]"
I parse the token
the result should be today's date

elements.name: Parsing tomorrow - [STARTDATE][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART]

steps.name: A date token "[TOMORROW]"
I parse the token
the result should be tomorrow's date

elements.name: Parsing yesterday - [STARTDATE][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART]

steps.name: A date token "[YESTERDAY]"
I parse the token
the result should be yesterday's date

elements.name: Parsing today minus two year and four month - [STARTDATE][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART]

steps.name: A date token "[TODAY-2YEAR-4MONTH]"
I parse the token
the result should be today's date minus two year and four month

elements.name: Parsing today minus one year and one month - [STARTDATE][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART]

steps.name: A date token "[TODAY-1YEAR-1MONTH]"
I parse the token
the result should be today's date minus one year and one month

elements.name: Parsing today minus one year, two months, and three days - [STARTDATE][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART]

steps.name: A date token "[TODAY-1YEAR-2MONTH-3DAY]"
I parse the token
the result should be today's date minus one year, two months, and three days

elements.name: Parsing today plus one year, minus one month, and plus one day - [STARTDATE][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART]

steps.name: A date token "[TODAY+1YEAR-1MONTH+1DAY]"
I parse the token
the result should be today's date plus one year, minus one month, and plus one day

elements.name: Parsing today minus one year and one month with regex - [STARTDATE][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART]

steps.name: A date token "[TODAY-1YEAR-1MONTH]"
I parse the token
the result should be today's date minus one year and one month

elements.name: Parsing today plus two years - [STARTDATE][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART]

steps.name: A date token "[TODAY+2YEAR]"
I parse the token
the result should be today's date plus two years

elements.name: Parsing today plus five months - [STARTDATE][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART]

steps.name: A date token "[TODAY+5MONTH]"
I parse the token
the result should be today's date plus five months

elements.name: Parsing tomorrow plus five months - [STARTDATE][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART]

steps.name: A date token "[TOMORROW+5MONTH]"
I parse the token
the result should be tomorrow's date plus five months

elements.name: Parsing yesterday plus five months and minus one year - [STARTDATE][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART]

steps.name: A date token "[YESTERDAY+5MONTH-1YEAR]"
I parse the token
the result should be yesterday's date plus five months and minus one year

elements.name: Handling null or invalid token input - [STARTDATE][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART][+ve/-ve][DATEPART]

steps.name: An invalid date range string "INVALID-TOKEN"
I parse the token
an error should be thrown with message "Invalid string token format : INVALID-TOKEN"
